Package org.tedros.fx.annotation.control

Annotation Type TButtonField

  • @Retention(RUNTIME)
@Target(FIELD)
public @interface TButtonField
     Build a TButton component.
 
 Example:
 
 @TButtonField(labeled = @TLabeled(text="Logout", parse = true),
 buttonBase=@TButtonBase(onAction=LogoutEventBuilder.class))
 private SimpleStringProperty logout;
 
 The event example:
 
 public class LogoutEventBuilder extends TBaseEventHandlerBuilder<ActionEvent>{
                @Override
                public EventHandler<ActionEvent> build() {
                        return  e -> {
                                //code here
                                ...
                        };
                }
 }
    Author:
    Davis Gordon
    See Also:
    TBaseEventHandlerBuilder

      • defaultButton

        boolean defaultButton
         Button Class
 
  Sets the value of the property defaultButton. 
  
  Property description: 
  A default Button is the button that receives a keyboard VK_ENTER press, 
  if no other node in the scene consumes it.
        Default:
        false

      • cancelButton

        boolean cancelButton
         Button Class
 
  Sets the value of the property cancelButton. 
  
  Property description: 
  A Cancel Button is the button that receives a keyboard VK_ESC press,

        Default:
